Participation at a scientific conference and critical reflection of the experience in a doctoral seminar.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to discuss with students who have already attended one or two conferences to which extent scientific conference fulfils the role of a scientific communication, how and to which extent doctoral student benefits from attending a conference and how to benefit the most from next conferences. It is the follow-up course to Scientific Conference as Professional Communication. For passing the course student has to write a 10 minutes presentation including critical analysis of  a conference and to present an abstract and materials used for the presentation (slides, transparencies, handouts, text of the presentation, etc). Conference experience should be new and different from that of SOZU.00.009.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students acquire the skills to critically analyse a scientific conference, their own presentation and the feedback they received to their project.
